## 9. Conclusion

This project demonstrates how machine learning can be effectively used to predict heart disease. The use of multiple models and feature scaling significantly improved performance. The Random Forest model achieved higher accuracy, making it more suitable for this problem.

Machine learning can assist healthcare professionals in early diagnosis and decision-making.

